# Resources & Data-Driven Design

Full strategy: [docs/CONTENT.md](../../docs/CONTENT.md).

## Rule

Gameplay values live in Resources (`.tres`), not code.

Use Resources for:

- Weapons
- Enemies
- Items
- Abilities / Skills
- Stats
- Buffs
- Loot tables
- Projectiles

## Pattern

Define a typed Resource:

```gdscript
class_name WeaponData
extends Resource

@export var display_name: String
@export var damage: float
@export var cooldown: float
@export var projectile_scene: PackedScene
```

Consume it in gameplay code:

```gdscript
@export var weapon_data: WeaponData

func attack() -> void:
    if not weapon_data:
        push_warning("Weapon has no data")
        return
    _spawn_projectile(weapon_data.projectile_scene, weapon_data.damage)
```

## Forbidden

- Hardcoded gameplay values in scripts (e.g. `damage = 25` inline).
- Large content collections stored in Markdown. Use `.tres` or JSON per [docs/CONTENT.md](../../docs/CONTENT.md).

## Save-Ability

Resource data used at runtime must be saveable if it changes. Static definitions (base weapon stats) are not saved; instance state (current durability, upgrades) is.
